  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Hygiene and Sanitation Response in Bokolymayo Camp</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In response to the critical WASH needs evident in Boqolmayo Camp, International Medical Corps intends to support Administration for Refugee and Returnee Affairs (ARRA) and UNHCR to meet urgent hygiene and sanitation needs through technical, material and logistical support.  The project will work to improve hygiene and sanitation infrastructure conditions in the camp and promote behavioral change to address poor hygiene and sanitation practices particularly among acutely malnourished children and other at-risk populations. International Medical Corps will support ARRA and UNHCR through the provision of necessary technical support to sanitarians and community volunteers to promote behavioral change.</narrative>
  </description>
